# UI Rule: No native `<select multiple>`

Do not use native HTML multi-select controls (`<select multiple>`).

## Why

- Poor usability on Windows and mobile
- Hard to scan selected items
- Inconsistent keyboard/mouse behavior across browsers

## Use this instead

Use the existing **checkbox dropdown** pattern used by incident dashboards:

- Button showing a summary label (e.g. `ทั้งหมด`, `เลือก N หน่วยงาน`, or the single selected name)
- Popover panel with a scrollable list of checkboxes
- Close on outside click and `Escape`
- Empty selection means **All** (do not store “select all” as a huge explicit array unless needed)

